00:40.106 --> 00:46.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And how urban revival is meeting
a crisis
of success -- a look at why
cities are being

00:46.046 --> 00:48.048 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
dragged down by class divides.

00:48.081 --> 00:51.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD FLORIDA, Author, "The
New Urban Crisis":
If the old urban crisis was
about the middle-class

00:51.184 --> 00:56.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
flight from the city to the
suburbs, the new
urban crisis is about really the
disappearance

00:56.189 --> 00:58.558 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of middle-class neighborhoods
from our society.

00:58.591 --> 01:02.228 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:02.262 --> 01:06.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:06.466 --> 01:19.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
