Trump today,
a declaration: The United States
wants out

01:19.212 --> 01:24.350 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the Paris accord on climate
change, and
wants to negotiate better terms.

01:24.384 --> 01:30.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Under the existing agreement,
the U.S. must
cut carbon emissions 26 to 28
percent from

01:30.490 --> 01:33.726 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
2005 levels by the year 2025.

01:33.760 --> 01:39.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But in the White House Rose
Garden, Mr. Trump
said the deal gives other
countries an economic

01:39.732 --> 01:42.202 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
edge and makes America foot the
bill.

01:42.235 --> 01:45.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
As president, I can put no other
consideration

01:45.972 --> 01:51.478 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
before the well-being of
American citizens.

01:51.511 --> 01:56.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Paris climate accord is
simply the latest
example of Washington entering
into an agreement

01:56.816 --> 02:04.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that disadvantages the United
States, to the
exclusive benefit of other
countries, leaving

02:04.491 --> 02:12.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
American workers, who I love,
and taxpayers
to absorb the cost in terms of
lost jobs,

02:12.565 --> 02:20.039 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
lower wages, shuttered factories
and vastly
diminished economic production.

02:20.073 --> 02:28.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Thus, as of today, the United
States will
cease all implementation of the
nonbinding

02:28.982 --> 02:37.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Paris accord and the draconian
financial and
economic burdens the agreement
imposes on

02:38.024 --> 02:39.159 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our country.

02:39.192 --> 02:43.696 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
At what point does America get
demeaned?

02:43.730 --> 02:47.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At what point do they start
laughing at us
as a country?

02:47.901 --> 02:55.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We want fair treatment for its
citizens and
we want fair treatment for our
taxpayers.

02:55.408 --> 03:03.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We don't want other leaders and
other countries
laughing at us anymore, and they
won't be.

03:03.116 --> 03:04.751 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
They won't be.

03:04.784 --> 03:12.058 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I was elected to represent the
citizens of
Pittsburgh, not Paris.

03:12.091 --> 03:16.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Former President
Obama said
today that Mr. Trump is joining
the handful

03:17.030 --> 03:19.532 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of nations that reject the
future.

03:19.566 --> 03:24.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, European leaders
voiced regret,
and said the accord cannot be
renegotiated.

03:24.804 --> 03:30.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
China, the world's largest
carbon emitter
right now, reaffirmed its
commitment to the

03:30.043 --> 03:31.411 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
deal.

03:31.444 --> 03:34.814 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we will hear from both sides
of the issue
after the news summary.

03:34.847 --> 03:39.919 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
