do just that,
but the White House said that
waiting might

03:48.161 --> 03:52.298 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
improve chances of peace between
Israel and
the Palestinians.

03:52.332 --> 03:58.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At least 14 Trump White House
officials have
been granted waivers from ethics
rules.

03:58.972 --> 04:03.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Their names were posted last
night, under
pressure from the Office of
Government Ethics.

04:03.943 --> 04:09.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The officials include, among
others, Michael
Catanzaro, a former oil and gas
lobbyist who's

04:09.515 --> 04:13.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
now a senior energy policy aide,
and Shahira
Knight.

04:13.386 --> 04:19.292 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's a former lobbyist for
Fidelity Investments,
now working on tax reform.

04:19.325 --> 04:24.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Russia, President Vladimir
Putin acknowledged
today that what he called
patriotic Russian

04:24.397 --> 04:29.936 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
individuals may have launched
cyber-attacks
on the U.S., but he insisted
again that his

04:29.969 --> 04:32.972 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
government had no role in
election meddling.

04:33.006 --> 04:39.312 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Instead, speaking to
international journalists,
he blamed Russophobic hysteria
and perhaps

04:39.345 --> 04:41.114 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a smear campaign.

04:41.147 --> 04:44.717 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
VLADIMIR PUTIN, Russian
President (through
translator): I can imagine the
situation where

04:44.751 --> 04:48.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
