from the European
Union.

06:12.772 --> 06:18.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Wall Street pushed higher today
on signs that
businesses added more jobs in
May.

06:18.177 --> 06:24.717 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained 135
points to close at 21144.

06:24.751 --> 06:29.389 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose 48, and the S&amp;P
500 added
18.

06:29.422 --> 06:32.492 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
All three were record closes.

06:32.525 --> 06:37.497 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And the NBA finals start
tonight, with the
much-anticipated rematch between
the Golden

06:37.530 --> 06:41.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
State Warriors and the Cleveland
Cavaliers,
the reigning champions.

06:41.100 --> 06:47.807 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
